choices.text:
... To memory, the most important events since the independence of B&H until the present days is proclamation of independence, the achievement of equal rights in the B&H Army for the politicians, and the arrest of Radovan Karadžić and Ratko Mladic.

Do you think Bosnia will one day join the European Union? To what extent do Tito and Yugoslavia still play a role in today's political realities in Serbia and Montenegro? Failure to finally resolve the post-Tito political system will clearly set a precedent for the Balkans and the whole region, and a complicated future for making all the necessary compromises in resolving the remaining problems. Even though the decision to enter is unfavorable at first glance, the continuation of Milosevic type nationalism will benefit bureocracy because it allows it to continue to exploit and mistreat its populace and even the Serbian people will be that much harder to provide them with truly democratic and better living conditions. Serbia is in search for a proper identity, between nationalism, social democracy and a capitalist system. Yugoslavia as a state doesn’t play any role now, but certain ways of management and constitutions of the old Yugoslavia are refurbishing neglected institutions of Serbia and Montenegro. From legal perspective Yugoslavia no longer exists. But many people who grew up in the Yugoslavia that existed some 25 years ago are still reacting to it.
